formPath.description: Path to display the form at.

items.description: Items to populate the list with

listPath.description: Path to display the list of items at

message.description: Message to display at top of page

renderForm.description:
Function to render the form when at form path.
This function will be passed the selected item
if an item is selected. Otherwise an empty object.

renderList.description:
Function to render the list when at list path.
Will be passed items and a function that sets the
pages selected item.

showAdd.description:
If true, the add button will be shown when at
list page.

title.description: Title to show at top of page

to.description: The address this item links to.

text.description: Text to display on the item

customerName.description: Name of the customer that placed the order

items.description: The menu items that belong to the order

orderCreated.description: The date the order was created.

updateAction.description:
Action to update the order. This is called when the next
button is clicked. Is given the id of the order and an object
containing the new order stage.

onClick.description:
Function that is called with the index of the item that
was clicked on.

id.description: Id of customer to update. Will change form title if provided.

onSubmit.description:
Function to call when on submit.
Passed an object that contains the input data
and the id if provided.

addAction.description:
Function to be called when the user submits the form to add
a customer.

customers.description: Customers to populate the list of customers with.

deleteAction.description: Function to be called when the user clicks on a customers delete button.

location.description:
Location proptype provided by route.
Don't provide manually.

updateAction.description:
Function to be called when the user submits the form to update
a customer.

fetchAction.description:
Function that is called when the component loads. Fetches
the orders.

orders.description: The orders to populate the page with.

customers.description: List of customers to be displayed

onDelete.description:
Function to be called when the delete button on a
customer is clicked.

onSelect.description: Function to be called when a customer is clicked on

render.description: Function to render each customer. e.g to wrap in links.

admins.description: Admin objects to populate the list with.

fetchAdmins.description: Action to call which fetches admins.

clearOnSubmit.description: If true all fields will be cleared when the form is submitted.

onSubmit.description:
Function to be called when the submit button is pressed.
This function will be given an object containing a property
and value for each input in children.

onValueChange.description:
An optional function that will be called with the new state
of the setting page. The function should return the new state.

submitText.description: The text that will appear on the submit button.

title.description: Title that will appear on top of page.

itemString.description:
Function that takes an item and returns a string
to represent the function in the list.

onClick.description:
Function to be called when an item is clicked on.
Function will receive the item.

title.description: Title to appear at top of list.

children.description: Should all be SettingsMenuItems. Item in the menu.

title.description: Title that appears at the top of the menu.

onClick.description:
Function that will be called when an item is clicked
on. Given the index of the item.

home.description: Home location of the menu button

homeIcon.description: Icon to display when at home

to.description: Location to go to when the button is clicked

toIcon.description: Icon to display when at to

onForward.description: Function to be called when the button is clicked when at home.

onBack.description: Function to be called  when the button is clicked when at to.

addAction.description:
Function to be called when the user submits the form to add
an item.

deleteAction.description: Function to be called when the user clicks on a menu items delete button.

items.description: Items to populate the list of menu with.

location.description:
Location proptype provided by route.
Don't provide manually.

updateAction.description:
Function to be called when the user submits the form to update
an item.

uploadImage.description: Function to call to upload a menu item image

menu.description: The list of menu items to display

onSelect.description:
Function to be called when a menu item
is clicked on. Will be passed the menu item.

onDelete.description:
Function to be called when the menu items delete
button is clicked on. Will not show delete button if
this function isn't provided. Passed the menu number
of the item

render.description:
Optional render function for each menu item. Passed
the menu item. Could be used to wrap the items in links
for example.

onClick.description: Function to be called when clicked on.

title.description: The title of the menu item.

menuNumber.description: The menu number of the menu item.

index.description: Index of the customer in the customer list

onDelete.description:
Function called when the on delete button is clicked.
If this prop is not provided a delete button isn't displayed.
Passed the id prop

onSelect.description:
Function called when the component is clicked on anywhere
besides the delete button. Function is passed:
(id, firstName, lastName, address, email)

id.description: Id of the user if modifying a user.

onSubmit.description:
Function to be called when the form is submitted. Is given
an object with the username and password that was entered. As
well as the users id if modifying a user.

username.description: Username of the user if modifying.

name.description: Name used for check box value when page is submitted

onChange.description: Used by Setting Page, don't set manually

value.description: Initial value of the check box.

fullWidth.description: If true, the input will take up the full width of its container.

label.description: Label content to be displayed on the input.

multiline.description: If true input will appear on multiple lines if long enough

name.description:
Name used to reference the inputs value in onSubmit of the parent
SettingPage component. All SettingPageInput children of a
SettingPage must have a unique name.

onChange.description: Receives this prop from parent SettingPage component. Don't set manually.

required.description: If true the label is displayed as required.

type.description: The type of the input element.

value.description: Received this prop from parent SettingPage component. Don't set manually.

getOptions.description:
Function to get options. The function is passed the
current state of the form with the values of all the form inputs.
This function should return an array of shape [[value, name]...]
for the options. If this prop is given the options prop will be ignored.

name.description: Name that will be used for the value when submitting.

onChange.description: Provided by Setting page, don't set manually.

options.description:
Array of shape [[value, name]...] that will be used to
populate the select list. This property will be ignored if
getOptions is provided.

state.description:
The state of the SettingPage. Provided by setting page,
don't set manually

onClick.description:
Function to be called when the item is
clicked on. Given by the SettingList this
item belongs to.

text.description:
Text representing the object this item represents.
Given by the SettingList this item belongs to.

onClick.description:
Prop provided by the parent. SettingsMenu
Dont set manually.

to.description:
If provided the menu item will be a link to the
address specified in this prop.

onSelect.description:
Function to be called when the menu item
is clicked on. (Anywhere but the delete button)

onDelete.description:
Function to be called when the delete button
is clicked.

id.description: Id of the menu item to upload the image for.

uploadImage.description:
Function to upload the file. Given the id of the
menu item and the file to upload.
